

Nepali government endorsed Thursday the latest six-point agreement between the Seven Party Alliance (SPA) and guerrillas.

The meeting of council of ministers was held on Thursday morning approving the pact singed on Wednesday midnight.

Prime Minister Koirala, on the occasion, briefed about the agreement to the ministers and sought their commitments to implement the pact.

Meanwhile, Koirala also informed about the agreement to the parliament on Thursday noon.

In his speech to the parliament he said that the pact had added extra responsibility to all parties involved and stressed on the need to work united.

He also warned of conspiracy that the reactionary forces might hatch to destroy the historic pact.

Koirala urged the guerrillas to create fearless environment as earliest as possible.

